06/11/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The country's chief negotiator with the EU, Vasile Puscas, said Tuesday (5 November) that Romania is ready to close another four chapters in accession talks with the EU: Telecommunication, Customs Union, Free Movement of Capital and Culture and Audiovisual Policy. Romania has opened 28 EU negotiation chapters and has so far closed 13 on a provisional basis. Following talks with Romanian representatives, the head of the EC Delegation to Romania, Jonathan Scheele, said that the EC would soon finalise the road map for Romania that will be adopted during the Union's December summit in Copenhagen. (Rompres - 05/11/02)
